			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Actually, the Color Flux spells are great for soloing. Even with just Color Flux it gives you an actual chance to get another spell off. And every time you stun them is at least one more shot you don't take while you and your pet are biffing on them.<BR>
A very important note: If you cast Color Flux the instant the enemy starts casting, YOU INTERRUPT THEIR SPELL!<BR>
I do it all the time. I wait until I see the pretty lights start coming from their hands, hit the hotkey, and as fast as the casting time is on it I can use it to interrupt them for a change. =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
