				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, I have very little experience with this spell, but what I have - like.  <BR>
<BR>
A friend and I were in Sol A (both 25th level) looking for 4 to round out our group.  We stayed very close to the zone, but managed to get a couple of trains coming at us anyway.  We managed to kill several members of the train before we got low enough to zone - and the only reason was that I was able to keep the buggers at bay with this spell.  Alone, this spell is useful for &quot;staying with&quot; a mob long enough to kill, loot and get exp before zoning and also gives a great opportunity to gate.  (I was forced to use this once last night - and it saved my skin)<BR>
<BR>
I'm trying to get a group of guildmates (including another Enchanter) together for some serious killing using this and AE DD spells...<BR>

